===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[espaigneul]]'' (modern ''[[épagneul]]''), from Latin ''[[Hispaniolus]]'' ‘Spanish’, from ''[[Hispania]]'' ‘Spain’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈspænjəl/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#Any of various small [[breed]]s of [[gun dog]] having a broad [[muzzle]], long, wavy [[fur]] and long ears than hang at the side of the head, bred for [[flush]]ing and [[retrieve|retrieving]] [[game]].

